Proclamation under the Duties Act 2001

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 227(1)(d) of the Duties Act 2001 â€“

        (a) declare that the following are exempt from the payment of all duties under that Act:
                (i) Nursing Board of Tasmania;
                (ii) Parliamentary Superannuation and Retiring Benefits Trust;
                (iii) State Fire Commission;
                (iv) Tasmania Development and Resources Board;
                (v) Ambulance Tasmania;
                (va) . . . . . . . .
                (vi) Tasmanian Library Advisory Board;
                (vii) Tasmanian Qualifications Authority;;
                (viii) . . . . . . . .
                (ix) Botanical Gardens Board;
                (x) the Trustees of the Tasmanian Museum and Art Gallery;
        (b) declare that this proclamation takes effect on the day on which its making is notified in the Gazette.
25 June 2001

G. S. M. GREEN

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

DAVID CREAN

Treasurer

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 1 July 2001

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Treasury and Finance.
